Articles.Content:
Hi everyone I'm using Realism Overhaul with Real Solar System. I've also installed RP-0. But after installing that some engines disappeared. They were really useful. Should I uninstall the mod ? 

Also in Techtree I can see the engine but during the building I searched but couldn't find the engine(s)
You can't find the engines because RP-0 hides parts which are not configured for RP-0, and most parts are not, so they are hidden.

16 minutes ago, legoclone09 said:

You can't find the engines because RP-0 hides parts which are not configured for RP-0, and most parts are not, so they are hidden.

OK thanks then I'll remove rp-0

Edited March 14, 2016 by berkekrkn

No, RP-0 does not hide parts unless you specifically tell it to.

@berkekrkn what parts in particular?

2 hours ago, NathanKell said:

No, RP-0 does not hide parts unless you specifically tell it to.

@berkekrkn what parts in particular?

It hides some useless tanks but also some useful engines. When I remove RP-0 they appear again and when I reinstall they disappear again. For example (BE-4 ; RS68-A; RL60 these kind of engines.)

 RL 60 is an important engine for me. I'm carrying 16 tons of payload to moon and I need engines, that produce 200-300 Kn thrust and has 2-3 ignitions. And RL-60 is the only engine that meets this conditions. In RP-0  Ican't see it but without RP-0 iit appears.

Edited March 14, 2016 by berkekrkn

@berkekrkn If you have Filter Extensions, they are merely put in the Non-RP0 category, not hidden. If you don't have Filter Extensions then not even that. The only parts RP-0 actually hides are some miscellaneous SXT parts that RO doesn't support either.
